race.description: Book For Christmas Meeting Sat 6th Dec Mdn Plate
race.comment: DALT JAZ (1) couldn't go on with the job last time at Rockhampton but had been ticking along well prior, narrowly nabbed at Townsville two back after leading. Peaking fitness now on the quick back-up and is sure to give another bold sight. CHANCE (10) is a two-start maiden who looks close to a win after placing at both runs, the latest when third at Bowen. Strips fitter third-up and gets the key booking of Wiggins. Sure to be very competitive. JOHN'S ROAD (2) was a sharp improver here last start when second-up from a long spell, sticking on gamely into second. Nearing peak now and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. ZABOOG (6) was much better here last time when sent forward, fighting on bravely to hold onto second. Deserves some respect off that. INCISIVE IVY (7) steps out on debut and is worth a market watch.
